MF = 3  NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS                                    5253 1451
  BELOW 7.2 EV, THE CAPTURE AND ELASTIC SCATTERING CROSS SECTIONS 5253 1451
  WERE ASSUMED TO BE IN 1/V FORM AND CONSTANT, RESPECTIVELY.      5253 1451
  THE CAPTURE CROSS SECTION AT 0.0253 EV WAS DETERMINED BY THE    5253 1451
  SYSTEMATICS FROM NEIGHBORING TE ISOTOPES.  THE ELASTIC          5253 1451
  SCATTERING CROSS SECTION WAS ESTIMATED FROM R = 5.2 FM.         5253 1451
  UNRESOLVED RESONANCE PARAMETERS WERE GIVEN IN THE ENERGY RANGE  5253 1451
  FROM 7.2 EV TO 100 KEV.                                         5253 1451
                                                                  5253 1451
  ABOVE 100 KEV, THE SPHERICAL OPTICAL AND STATISTICAL MODEL      5253 1451
  CALCULATION WAS PERFORMED WITH CASTHY/2/, BY TAKING ACCOUNT OF  5253 1451
  COMPETING REACTIONS, OF WHICH CROSS SECTIONS WERE CALCULATED    5253 1451
  WITH PEGASUS/3/ STANDING ON A PREEQUILIBRIUM AND MULTI-STEP     5253 1451
  EVAPORATION MODEL.  THE OMP'S FOR NEUTRON GIVEN IN TABLE 1 WERE 5253 1451
  DETERMINED TO REPRODUCE A SYSTEMATIC TREND OF THE TOTAL CROSS   5253 1451
  SECTION BY CHANGING R0 AND RSO OF IIJIMA-KAWAI POTENTIAL/4/.    5253 1451
  THE OMP'S FOR CHARGED PARTICLES ARE AS FOLLOWS:                 5253 1451
     PROTON   = PEREY/5/                                          5253 1451
     ALPHA    = HUIZENGA AND IGO/6/                               5253 1451
     DEUTERON = LOHR AND HAEBERLI/7/                              5253 1451
     HELIUM-3 AND TRITON = BECCHETTI AND GREENLEES/8/             5253 1451
  PARAMETERS FOR THE COMPOSITE LEVEL DENSITY FORMULA OF GILBERT   5253 1451
  AND CAMERON/9/ WERE EVALUATED BY IIJIMA ET AL./10/   MORE       5253 1451
  EXTENSIVE DETERMINATION AND MODIFICATION WERE MADE IN THE       5253 1451
  PRESENT WORK.  TABLE 2 SHOWS THE LEVEL DENSITY PARAMETERS USED  5253 1451
  IN THE PRESENT CALCULATION.  ENERGY DEPENDENCE OF SPIN CUT-OFF  5253 1451
  PARAMETER IN THE ENERGY RANGE BELOW E-JOINT IS DUE TO GRUPPELAAR5253 1451
  /11/.                                                           5253 1451
